  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "material",
    "intended": "Let $0=a_0<a_1<a_2<\\cdots$ be the sequence of integers defined by $a_0=0$ and $a_1=1$, and $a_{k+1}$ is the smallest integer $n$ for which the number of solutions to $a_i+a_j \\leq n$ (with $0\\leq i\\leq j\\leq k$ and $j\\geq 1$) is $<n$.\n\nIs the number of solutions to $a_i+a_j \\leq x$ equal to $x+O(x^{1/4+o(1)})$?",
